metadata.description:
Ironically, LOVE SONGS was inspired by my life as a singer songwriter, performing countless love songs on countless stages but without someone to look for in the front row that I can call my own.

Produced by: Alex Sacco & Sammy Arriaga
Written by: Sammy Arriaga, Aaron Scherz & Alex Sacco

Art: NoManaArt

lyrics.text:
LOVE SONGS

(Interlude)

V1
I heard that my best friend just got a new girlfriend,
I wish em both the best, you know I really do,
Seems love is in the air, 
You gotta tell me where,
Cause it don’t seem fair

PRE1
That I'm singing to a ghost, 
To a girl nobody knows,
Damn the thought just gets me low,
Ooo, I’m so tired...

HOOK
Of singing these love songs for no one, I’m so done,
What’s the point of pouring my heart out if their ain’t no one?
For just once I want someone I could wrap my words around,
The Irony ain’t lost on me,
Why’s it gotta be mr. lonely?
Singing these love songs for no one!

V2
Every now & then in between my sets,
They ask me where I get my inspiration from,
They say she must be fine, 
That I’m a lucky guy,
Never tell em it’s my...

PRE2
Imagination runnin’ wild, 
Yeah I crack a little smile,
Damn I hate I gotta lie,
Ooo, I’m so tired...

HOOK

BRIDGE:
Imma find her, she gon’ find me,
Maybe while I’m strummin’ these strings,
Imma find her, she gon’ find me,
Me, yeah, yeah (x2)

HOOK
